author: butek
msg: I added --all to WSDL2Java.  I thought it would be quick and easy.  Silly me.  This
option exposed some bugs I had to fix.  I also added a quick test.

author: tomj
msg: Update the handling of literal message parts to handle either
the element= or type= declaration (e.g. <part name="foo" type="ns:myType">).

author: tomj
msg: Check the Java mangled XML name when looking for bean elements.
WSDL2Java mangles the element names per JAX-RPC, but we wont find those names
in the XML we process.  This change lets us find them.
